sentences.sentence: There are at least nine physiographic cycles in the middle reaches of the Yellow River during the Late Cenozoic Era.
sentences.translation: 在晚新生代黄河中游至少存在九个地文期旋回。

sentences.sentence: The Natural History Museum, an integral part of the Institute, was founded at the same time under the original name of Physiographic Museum.
sentences.translation: 同年建立的自然历史博物馆是该所的一部分，当时它的名称是自然地理博物馆。

sentences.sentence: The model can use to the similar area for physiographic condition, and to appraise the benefit of valley harnessing and soil and water conservation.
sentences.translation: 本模型可用于自然地理条件类似的地区，并可用来评价流域治理的效益和水土保持效益。
